    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-08T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-08T02:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-08T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 8, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 8—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Unless otherwise instructed I shall go to Shanghai taking with me Naval Attaché,
                    leaving <persName corresp="#p_ECVH1">Engert</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MEL1">Murray</persName> here. My British colleague and I believe
                    that our presence at Shanghai might help in current negotiations for peace.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping, Shanghai, Tokyo and commander in chief.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
